name: Scuttling Sliver
oracle_text: Sliver creatures you control have "{2}: Untap this creature."
flavor_text: A living fossil active after eons of dormancy.

name: Constricting Sliver
oracle_text: Sliver creatures you control have "When this creature enters the battlefield, you may exile target creature an opponent controls until this creature leaves the battlefield."
flavor_text: Slivers are often seen toying with enemies they capture, not out of cruelty, but to fully learn their physical capabilities.

name: Root Sliver
oracle_text:
This spell can't be countered.

flavor_text:
"It would take another apocalypse to stop the slivers now."
—Riptide Project researcher

name: Lightning Strike
oracle_text: Lightning Strike deals 3 damage to any target.

name: Kaito, Dancing Shadow
oracle_text:
Whenever one or more creatures you control deal combat damage to a player, you may return one of them to its owner's hand. If you do, you may activate loyalty abilities of Kaito twice this turn rather than only once.

0: Draw a card.

name: Thought-Knot Seer
oracle_text:
({C} represents colorless mana.)
When Thought-Knot Seer enters the battlefield, target opponent reveals their hand. You choose a nonland card from it and exile that card.
When Thought-Knot Seer leaves the battlefield, target opponent draws a card.

name: Leeching Sliver
oracle_text: Whenever a Sliver you control attacks, defending player loses 1 life.
flavor_text:
"Seeing one slowly devour one of my party begged the question—do they know what cruelty is?"
—Hastric, Thunian scout

name: Muscle Sliver
oracle_text: All Sliver creatures get +1/+1.
flavor_text: The air was filled with the cracks and snaps of flesh hardening as the new sliver joined the battle.

name: Plague Sliver
oracle_text: All Slivers have "At the beginning of your upkeep, this permanent deals 1 damage to you."
flavor_text: A sliver shares everything with its hive—even its afflictions.

name: Basal Sliver
oracle_text: All Slivers have "Sacrifice this permanent: Add {B}{B}."
flavor_text:
"Fascinating . . . These creatures display the paradox of tenacity and purposed self-destruction I have sought to breed into my thrulls."
—Endrek Sahr, master breeder

name: Dregscape Sliver
oracle_text:
Each Sliver creature card in your graveyard has unearth {2}.
Unearth {2} ({2}: Return this card from your graveyard to the battlefield. It gains haste. Exile it at the beginning of the next end step or if it would leave the battlefield. Unearth only as a sorcery.)
flavor_text:
"A colony of horrors lurks beneath the mire. One must move deliberately with every ste—"
—Loamlair guide, last words

name: Homing Sliver
oracle_text:
Each Sliver card in each player's hand has slivercycling {3}.
Slivercycling {3} ({3}, Discard this card: Search your library for a Sliver card, reveal it, put it into your hand, then shuffle.)
flavor_text:
"Where did *you* come from?"
—Otarian hunter, last words

name: Necrotic Sliver
oracle_text: All Slivers have "{3}, Sacrifice this permanent: Destroy target permanent."
flavor_text: Though Volrath is long dead, the slivers have become everything he wanted them to be: mindless instruments of destruction and despair.

name: Pulmonic Sliver
oracle_text:
All Sliver creatures have flying.
All Slivers have "If this permanent would be put into a graveyard, you may put it on top of its owner's library instead."
flavor_text: Like a great bellows it hisses, and its kin, both living and dead, are lifted to safety.

name: Shadow Sliver
oracle_text: All Sliver creatures have shadow. (They can block or be blocked by only creatures with shadow.)
flavor_text: These slivers, trapped between worlds since the Rathi overlay, are among the last to claim direct lineage from the lost Sliver Queen.

name: Quick Sliver
oracle_text:
Flash
Any player may cast Sliver spells as though they had flash.
flavor_text: The directors of the Riptide Project wanted instant results on the sliver experiments. They got their wish.

name: Telekinetic Sliver
oracle_text: All Slivers have "{T}: Tap target permanent."
flavor_text:
"Slivers are guided only by simple instinct. Advance the hive, and you will be welcomed. Impede the hive, and you will face unrelenting opposition."
—Freyalise

name: Toxin Sliver
oracle_text: Whenever a Sliver deals combat damage to a creature, destroy that creature. It can't be regenerated.
flavor_text: It doesn't need to use its venom—it just needs you to know it can.

name: Virulent Sliver
oracle_text: All Sliver creatures have poisonous 1. (Whenever a Sliver deals combat damage to a player, that player gets a poison counter. A player with ten or more poison counters loses the game.)
flavor_text:
"They actually have venom, not poison. If they were poisonous, a single drop would—IT BURNS! IT BURNS!"
—Riptide researcher, last words
